                                    <h2 class="static-title">Citizen Academy</h2>                                   
                                  <p>A Boston Cares initiative focused on facilitating the shift from casual volunteering to intentional citizenship. </p>
                                        <p>Learn more about the issues that affect you and the community. Citizen Academy is designed to provide opportunities for individuals to learn more about contemporary social issues encountered in our communities and through our volunteer service.</p>
                                        <h3>Programs</h3>
                                        <h4><strong>Serve &amp; Learn</strong></h4>
                                  <p>Serve &amp; Learn Projects are one-time volunteer opportunities that include an educational component to better understand the issue being addressed. Either before or after the project, there will be time set aside to:</p>
                                        <ul>
                                          <li>Hearing from a staff person from the organization;</li>
                                          <li>Having a special talk from a guest speaker;</li>
                                          <li>Engaging in a facilitated group discussion; or</li>
                                          <li>Participating in a service learning activity.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <p><strong>TeamWorks</strong></p>
                                        <p>TeamWorks fuses volunteer projects with team-building activities and issue education to create a cycle of learning and friendship. Most TeamWorks projects require that volunteers commit to serve together for 4-6 projects, over 2-3 months; however, there are other TeamWorks which require a shorter time commitment with fewer projects. All participants will gather at a kickoff to create a schedule of projects combined with a few social activities to participate in together.  Boston Cares will arrange these projects and they will be led by Project Leaders.</p>
                                        <h4><strong>Social Cinema</strong>
                                         
                                        <p>Social Cinema screenings are part of PBS' Emmy winning series Independent Lens, a    monthly film series hosted in partnership with Boston Cares, ITVS   Community Cinema, and City Year.</p></h4>
                                        <h4><strong>Explorations</strong></h4>
                                        <p>Explorations is a monthly series offering free tours in different neighborhoods and historical buildings throughout Boston. Boston has a rich history and a lively culture that is not always apparent to the naked eye. This is a great way to get to know the city the people and events that have shaped it into what it is today.</p>
                                        <p>Examples of past Explorations programs include: The Black Heritage Trail, the South End, and the Mary Baker Eddy Library for the Betterment of Humanity. Throughout the tour, participants are encouraged to ask questions. After the tour, participants are invited to a social component of the program, where they can grab lunch of a cup of coffee at a local caf√© </p> 
                                     
                                        <h3><p>For more information, please contact:</p>
                                        <p>Rachel Fontana, Civic Engagement Coordinator VISTA</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">617-422-0910, ext. 207     </p>
                                  <p><a href="mailto:rfontana@bostoncares.org">rfontana@bostoncares.org</a></p></h3>
                                  
